HEADWORD: Lessener
<hw>Less"en*er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or
that which, lessens.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His wife . . . is the <qex>lessener</qex> of his pain, and the
augmenter of his pleasure.</q> <rj><qau>J. Rogers (1839).
</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lessening</ent>⟦br⟧
